
[1]coloring

   COLORING, ppr.

   1. Dying; staining; tinging.

   2. Giving a fair external appearance; palliating; excusing.

                                COLORING, n.

   1. The act or art of dyeing; the state of being colored; color.

   2. A specious appearance; fair artificial representation; as, the story
   has a coloring of truth.

   3. Among painters, the manner of applying colors; or the mixture of
   light and shade, formed by the various colors employed.
